        <item>Start with protein- and fiber-rich foods: vegetables, eggs, fish. Avoid quick sugars to limit blood sugar spikes.</item>
        <item>Unsweetened coffee and tea are usually fine while fasting. Listen to your body if you are sensitive to caffeine.</item>
        <item>Hunger often comes in waves. Wait 15–20 minutes, drink water and stay busy — it often passes on its own.</item>
        <item>Enough sleep makes fasting easier. Avoid very large meals right before bed during your eating window.</item>
